### Welcome to the RAML API portal for the <a href="https://mail.google.com" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="32px"> GMail API</a>! 

This portal provides 
- a [RAML spec](/apiplatform/repository/public/organizations/30/apis/7881/versions/8035/files/root) describing the GMail API in a clear, human- and machine-readable format
- [documentation](/apiplatform/popular/#/portals/apis/7881/versions/8035/pages/6645) of the GMail API auto-generated from the RAML spec
- the [documentation](/apiplatform/popular/#/portals/apis/7881/versions/8035/pages/6645) is live: you can make calls to the GMail API from the documentation
- live, documented usecases for the GMail API, provided as API notebooks, and exercising much of the GMail API

_This portal is built on the Anypoint Platform for APIs, using RAML version 0.8._

_For more information about RAML, see [http://raml.org](http://raml.org)._

_The API notebooks are all executable! Hit "enter" in any code cell to execute it (and all cells before it that have not executed yet), or scroll to the bottom of the notebook and click "Play notebook". For more information, see [http://apinotebook.com](http://apinotebook.com)._

---
### Please note:

This portal and its contents are not affiliated with GMail. They are, however, useful for working with, and learning about, the GMail API.

The official developer API portal for GMail is at <a href="https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/v1/reference/s.box.com/" target="_blank">https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/v1/reference/</a>
